## FileTree Component

This component renders a hierarchical file tree structure, commonly used in documentation sites or file explorers. It supports nested folders and files, with visual indicators for folder states (open/closed) and active files.

### Purpose

The `FileTree` component is responsible for displaying a navigable tree of file and folder nodes. It allows users to expand and collapse folders to reveal their contents and select individual files.

### Key Exports

*   `FileTree`: The main React component for rendering the file tree.

### Props for `FileTree`

*   `nodes` (`TreeNode[]`): An array of `TreeNode` objects, representing the root level of the file tree. Each node can be either a `FolderNode` or a `FileNode`.
*   `activeKey` (`string | null`): The key of the currently active file in the tree. This is used to visually highlight the selected file.
*   `onSelect` (`(key: string) => void`): A callback function that is called when a file node is clicked. It receives the `key` of the selected file.
*   `depth` (`number`, optional, defaults to `0`): An internal prop used to manage indentation levels for nested nodes. Users of the component typically do not need to provide this.

### Internal Components

*   `FolderRow`: Renders a single folder row, including its name, an expand/collapse toggle (chevron icon), and recursively renders its children using `FileTree`.
*   `FileRow`: Renders a single file row, including its name and an icon. It highlights the row if its `key` matches the `activeKey`.
*   `FolderIcon`: Renders an SVG icon for a folder, changing its appearance based on whether it's open or closed.
*   `FileIcon`: Renders an SVG icon for a file.

### Usage Example

```tsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { FileTree } from './doc-repo-template/src/FileTree';
import type { TreeNode } from './doc-repo-template/src/lib/tree';

const sampleNodes: TreeNode[] = [
  {
    kind: 'folder',
    name: 'src',
    children: [
      {
        kind: 'folder',
        name: 'components',
        children: [
          { kind: 'file', name: 'Button.tsx', key: 'button-ts', title: 'Button Component' },
          { kind: 'file', name: 'Modal.tsx', key: 'modal-ts', title: 'Modal Component' },
        ]
      },
      { kind: 'file', name: 'App.tsx', key: 'app-ts', title: 'App Entry Point' },
      { kind: 'file', name: 'index.ts', key: 'index-ts', title: 'Index File' },
    ]
  },
  {
    kind: 'folder',
    name: 'lib',
    children: [
      { kind: 'file', name: 'tree.ts', key: 'tree-ts', title: 'Tree Node Definitions' },
    ]
  },
  { kind: 'file', name: 'README.md', key: 'readme-md', title: 'Project Readme' },
];

function App() {
  const [activeFileKey, setActiveFileKey] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const handleSelectFile = (key: string) => {
    setActiveFileKey(key);
    // Add logic here to load content based on the selected file
    console.log('Selected file:', key);
  };

  return (
    <div style={{ width: '300px', border: '1px solid #ccc', padding: '10px' }}>
      <h2>File Explorer</h2>
      <FileTree 
        nodes={sampleNodes} 
        activeKey={activeFileKey} 
        onSelect={handleSelectFile} 
      />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```
